So what do I do? I search for the sharpest looking watches for the best price, and then I suggest them to you.

But here's the thing: I'm not just going to suggest popular brands. I've found dozens of watch companies that produce quality, affordable products you've probably never heard of--until now.
__
Because let's be real. You deserve a timepiece as unique and attractive as you are. And if you stick with me, I promise you'll get it.

Essential Fact #9:  So diver watches have a bezel, that turns around the watch-face. It only turns counterclockwise. Do you know why? Diver watches are used to track diving time. If your watch got bumped and turned clockwise, your watch would read that you have more oxygen that you actually have. The bezel turning only counterclockwise is a safety feature. Hmmmm. Interesting‚Ä¶.

Essential Fact #8:  The dagger in the heart of the pocket watch was twisted with World War II. Pocket watches were banned. ‚ÄúTwo hands on the rifle at all times‚Äù was the reason. Meh, pocket watches are for aristocratic prissy boys anyway‚Äînot strapping gents like us.

Essential Fact #7:  Most expensive watch? Made by Patrek Phillipe‚Äîsurprise, surprise.  It was auctioned for $11 million at an auction in November 2016. Only four of these 1940s era watches are known to exist in the world. Yeah. Not gunna push $11 million dollar watches on you.
Essential Fact #6:  Men started wearing wristwatches during the First World War. Of course, watches were made fashionable by the manliest of men‚Äîand they still are.

Essential Fact #5:  Jason Bourne‚Äôs (Matt Damon‚Äôs) choice of watch? TAG Heuer. A great choice. But of course, you can look just as strapping beating the hell out of Russians with much cheaper, just as sharp, watches choices.

Essential Fact #4:  Wristwatches were initially made for women, while men carried pocket watches. Well, obviously that‚Äôs changed. Yet another example of how women got it right before us. But damn, we wear them good now.

Essential Fact #3:  Next time you buy a watch, online or otherwise, take note of the time on the watch. In store, the two typical times that watches are set at are 2:50 or 10:10. This makes the watch resemble a smiley face (even called ‚ÄúHappy Time‚Äù). Supposedly, that subconsciously can raise your mood and encourage a purchase. WON‚ÄôT WORK ON US YOU WATCH-SELLING CROOKS! Alright, you‚Äôre not crooks. But we‚Äôre still only going to buy the best stuff.
Essential Fact #2:  Sean Connery is a Rolex guy. Daniel Craig is an Omega man. Bond men of great taste. BUT thankfully, you can look just as good with watches that are a fraction the price.

Essential Fact #1:  The first gents who told time? The Egyptians. They used Sundials. The studs built pyramids, wore make-up and now because of them, we‚Äôve got studly watches. Glad that make-up-on-men trend didn‚Äôt stick though.
